Nigeria’s duo of Edem Offiong and Jamiu Azeez are in the race for places in the main draw of the singles event at the 2019 ITTF Challenge Spanish Open, holding at the Palacio Multiusos Guadalajara, North Central city of Spain. Offiong, drawn in Group 14 of the women’s singles qualifying round, was in fine form against Portugal’s Andrade Raquel. Despite losing first game at 8-11, Offiong recovered to record an emphatic win of 11-5, 11-5, 11-8 to claim a 3-1 win. Like his compatriot – Italy-based Azeez overwhelmed Moldova’s Cissa Victor with 11-4, 11-7, 11-6. They are expected to play their last group matches today to determine their qualification to the main draw. Germany’s Ruwen Filus was the runner up in Minsk in 2015 when beaten by Qatar’s Li Ping in the final, his highest finish to date at an open international tournament, and the German is the top seed in the men’s singles event at the 2019 ITTF Challenge Spanish Open.